<section xml:id="sec-4-4-The_Slope_of_a_Line" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>The Slope of a Line</title>
    <p><em>Slope of a Line</em> gives the formal definition of slope in the standard notation and 
        covers examples of interpolation and extrapolation. It also foreshadows the point-point 
        form of a line, using the analytic geometry approach of finding the slope to an 
        arbitrary point (x, y).</p>
        
